The polarization-dependent direction of Fanh has a geometrical origin related to the Mo and S sublattices, which are displaced by the QIR in the opposite direction (Fig. 1c). The motion of QIR modulates the interlayer interaction, which is approximated by the springs connecting the Mo and the S atoms (S1, S2, S3) in the adjacent layers as illustrated in Fig. 3e. The associated interaction energy is \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
